function reformatNumber(number) {
    const cleanedNumber = number.replace(/\D/g, '');

    const blocks = [];
    let n = cleanedNumber.length;
    for (let i = 0; i < n;) {
        if (n - i === 2 || n - i === 4) {
            blocks.push(cleanedNumber.substr(i, 2));
            i += 2;
        } else {
            blocks.push(cleanedNumber.substr(i, 3));
            i += 3;
        }
    }

    return blocks.join('-');
}
```

    1. Remove all non-digit characters from the given phone number string.
2. Create a list called `blocks` which will store the number groups.
3. Loop through the cleaned number string:
   - If there are exactly 2 or 4 digits remaining, add a group of 2 digits to `blocks`.
   - Otherwise, add a group of 3 digits to `blocks`.
4. Join the groups in `blocks` with dashes and return the resulting string.

